An explosion followed bya fire ripped through a British Petroleum (BP) oil refinery,killing one man.    A BP spokesman said the fire was confined to one plant atthe 700-acre refinery at Grangemouth, 25 miles west ofEdinburgh. The cause and extent of the damage had yet to bedetermined.    Two people were killed in a previous explosion and fire atthe plant on March 13. That incident is still beinginvestigated, the spokesman said. REUTER&#3;